If the document has @dynamic-toc-type, it may not have a table-of-contents element. 
Site default applies if both @dynamic-toc-type attribute and table-of-contents element are omitted.

<issue-meta xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="./xsd/SCJATS-journalissue1-0.xsd" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" dynamic-toc-type="topic-driven"> 
-->
